1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,180
Day 7.

2
00:00:01,180 --> 00:00:03,638
I deleted a week's worth of code.

3
00:00:03,638 --> 00:00:04,500
Why?

4
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:07,277
Because it had been right for the wrong reason.

5
00:00:07,277 --> 00:00:08,722
I can't code.

6
00:00:08,722 --> 00:00:10,833
9 years in crypto.

7
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:13,041
AI trades my thousand.

8
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:14,291
Day 7.

9
00:00:14,291 --> 00:00:22,861
After yesterday's 90 percent win rate illusion collapsed, I made the most against-my-own-instincts decision I could — delete.

10
00:00:22,861 --> 00:00:24,208
Not bugs.

11
00:00:24,208 --> 00:00:26,166
The things I'd been right about.

12
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:27,638
A week of work.

13
00:00:27,638 --> 00:00:32,111
I hardcoded the grid feature off inside the system config.

14
00:00:32,111 --> 00:00:38,055
No future version of the code can turn it back on without me physically editing the system file.

15
00:00:38,055 --> 00:00:40,722
Ulysses pact with my future self.

16
00:00:40,722 --> 00:00:48,041
Then I wrote a new house rule — every strategy change requires a 90-day backtest before it touches a dollar.

17
00:00:48,041 --> 00:00:49,569
No exceptions.

18
00:00:49,569 --> 00:00:52,652
Performers protect their past rightness.

19
00:00:52,652 --> 00:00:54,291
Learners replace it.

20
00:00:54,291 --> 00:01:00,888
The ability to burn something you were right about — that's the thing that separates real learning from performance.

21
00:01:00,888 --> 00:01:04,611
Day 8 tomorrow — I told everyone I was wrong.

22
00:01:04,611 --> 00:01:06,069
Follow along.

